To calculate Return on Assets (ROA), I need to divide the Net Profit by the Total Assets.

Step 1: Identify the Net Profit from the income statement.
Net Profit = $3,744,117.89

Step 2: Calculate the average Total Assets.
Initial Total Assets (2023-12-31) = $28,000,000.00
End Total Assets (2024-02-05) = $39,772,748.32
Average Total Assets = ($28,000,000.00 + $39,772,748.32) / 2 = $33,886,374.16

Step 3: Calculate ROA by dividing Net Profit by Average Total Assets.
ROA = Net Profit / Average Total Assets
ROA = $3,744,117.89 / $33,886,374.16
ROA = 0.1105 or 11.05%

Therefore, the Return on Assets (ROA) is 11.05%.
